The paper deals with the design and routing of a quantum network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The use of virtual links to reduce the diameter of the network is a graph theory problem (cs.DC), and the paper also discusses the limitations of classical encryption protocols against quantum adversaries, which falls under the category of quantum information (quant-ph). Finally, the paper proposes a routing algorithm that has space and time complexity considerations, which is a topic in computer science (cs.SI).
